[250.683043, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[250.683862, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K       •      options enabled by \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K       •      shell aliases defined with \u001b[1malias\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K       •      various  process IDs, including those of background jobs, the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K              value of \u001b[1m$$\u001b[22m, and the value of \u001b[1mPPID\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K       When a simple command other than a builtin or shell function  is  to\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K       be  executed, it is invoked in a separate execution environment that\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       consists of the following.  Unless otherwise noted, the  values  are\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       inherited from the shell.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K       •      the  shell's open files, plus any modifications and additions\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K              specified by redirections to the command\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K       •      the current working directory\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[K       •      the file creation mode mask\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[19;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[20;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K       •      options enab"]
[250.684666, "o", "led by \u001b[1mshopt\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K       •      shell aliases defined with \u001b[1malias\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K       •      various  process IDs, including those of background jobs, the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K              value of \u001b[1m$$\u001b[22m, and the value of \u001b[1mPPID\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K       When a simple command other than a builtin or shell function  is  to\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K       be  executed, it is invoked in a separate execution environment that\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       consists of the following.  Unless otherwise noted, the  values  are\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       inherited from the shell.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K       •      the  shell's open files, plus any modifications and additions\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K              specified by redirections to the command\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K       •      the current working directory\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[K       •      the file creation mode mask\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[19;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[20;1H"]
[250.709603, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       •      parsing the value of \u001b[1m\u001b[7mSHELLOPT\u001b[27m\u001b[1mS \u001b[22mfrom the shell environment  at\u001b[m\r\n              startup\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      redirecting  output using the >, >|, <>, >&, &>, and >> redi‐\u001b[m\r\n              rection operators\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      using the \u001b[1mexec \u001b[22mbuiltin command to replace the shell with  an‐\u001b[m\r\n              other command\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      adding  or  deleting  builtin commands with the \u001b[1m-f \u001b[22mand \u001b[1m-d \u001b[22mop‐\u001b[m\r\n              tions to the \u001b[1menable \u001b[22mbuiltin command\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      using the \u001b[1menable \u001b[22mbuiltin command  to  enable  disabled  shell\u001b[m\r\n              builtins\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      specifying the \u001b[1m-p \u001b[22moption to the \u001b[1mcommand \u001b[22mbuiltin command\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       •      turning  off  restricted  mode  with  \u001b[1mset  +r \u001b[22mor \u001b[1mshopt -u re‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mstricted_shell\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 6791/6908 99% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
